        "timestamp": "2019-04-11 14:32:45.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nAdditional remarks: this patch fixes running Molecule _itself_ test for Docker role on Centos7.6 host. This didn't happen on Ubuntu as /dev/loop* nodes are preallocated upon system boot-up.\nSamuli: This is the fix for the issue we've been discussing (difference between Ubuntu and Centos platforms).\n\nAdditional package is required as on Centos default filesystem is xfs and while starting docker in docker in that case it errors due to lack of mkfs.ext4 binary (it says that overlayfs not supported on xfs or smthing similar).",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
